                           PROD TO DR 
When we are performing the DR drill it must not shuold to restore the messages data into DR 

Step by step Process of DR Drill

1. Export Queue Manager Configuration(PROD)
Ex Cmd: dmpmqcfg -m PROD_TFMQM > prod_tfmqm.mqsc

2. Backup Persistent Data
Stop the PROD queue manager cleanly
Cmd:endmqm -w PROD_TFMQM

Queue manager data directory (usually /var/mqm/qmgrs/PROD_TFMQM)

Log files (usually /var/mqm/log/PROD_TFMQM)
Cmd : tar -cvf prod_qmgr_backup.tar /var/mqm/qmgrs/PROD_QMGR /var/mqm/log/PROD_QMGR
3.Restore on DR:
tar -xvf prod_tfmqm_backup.tar -C /var/mqm/  
Note: DR QMGR should have same name 


4. Recreate MQ Objects
Apply the MQSC script on DR:
Cmd: runmqsc PROD_TFMQM < prod_tfmqm.mqsc

5 start Manager & validate(DR side) 
Cmd:amqsget QUEUE_NAME PROD_QMGR
runmqsc PROD_QMGR
DISPLAY CHSTATUS(*)

7. Redirect Applications
Update client connection strings or CCDT (Client Channel Definition Table) to point to DR host.


Note:
If u are using RDMQ(Replicated data QMANAGER) replication handles automatically you just need to start the DR instance.
